  "Notes": [
    {
      "Text": "Security update for bind",
      "Title": "Topic",
      "Type": "Summary"
    },
    {
      "Text": "This update for bind fixes the following issues\n\n- CVE-2026-3039: BIND 9 server memory exhaustion during GSS-API TKEY negotiation (bsc#1265591).\n- CVE-2026-3592: Amplification vulnerabilities via self-pointed glue records (bsc#1265592).\n- CVE-2026-5946: Invalid handling of CLASS != IN (bsc#1265594).\n- CVE-2026-5950: Unbounded resend loop in BIND 9 resolver (bsc#1265596).\n- CVE-2026-3593: Heap use-after-free vulnerability in BIND 9 DNS-over-HTTPS implementation (bsc#1265593).\n\nChanges for bind:\n\n- Update to release 9.18.49\n",
      "Title": "Details",
      "Type": "General"
    },
